9:
It's even more amazing than I
imagined!
13:
Yeah, a lot of people have that
reaction when they see this place
for the first time.
18:
It's so... bright and colorful! It almost
hurts my eyes!
22:
What's up, Light? Something the
matter?
26:
No, it's just... I wonder whether a city
as... stimulating as this is good for
the development of a young child.
30:
Grr... I thought I told you, I don't want
to be treated like a kid!
34:
I don't know about "stimulating," but
he's got a point. Folks in this place
are trigger happy, to put it lightly.
38:
Try to stick with us, so you don't get
lost, okay?
44:
O-okay! I definitely, absolutely won't
get lost this time!
50:
Err... So this is what passes for food
on this world?
54:
Yep. Don't knock it before you try it.
Have a bite.
58:
It seems... suspicious, but I suppose
it can't hurt.
70:
It tastes like... clay or something! Do
you actually eat this?
75:
That's just the base free version.
You've gotta shell out some cash to
bump up the flavor.
79:
Oh! Wow! It's the exact same food,
yet the taste is entirely different!
83:
They use some fancy technology to
reproduce real tastes and textures.
Does a good job of fooling your
taste buds.
87:
You mean... This food is an illusion of
some sort?
91:
Er, not quite. I don't know how they
do it exactly, to be honest. Might be
better to ask someone like Regis.
96:
I'll make sure to do that later. I might
be able to use the techniques in my
own magic.
101:
You sure that's a good idea? If you're
trying to steer clear of "suspicious
creeps," he'd be high on my list of
who to avoid.
121:
It seems that way... And a lot of
them, at that. They must have
escaped from somewhere nearby.
125:
Well, no getting out of this fight.
Time to kick some ass.
141:
I'm sorry, I'm... fine, really! That just
took me by surprise.
145: No holding back! Here I go!
151:
Looks like nobody else was injured.
Good thing we managed to keep
damage down to a minimum.
155:
You did excellently as well, Kyoka.
That was some precise movement
on your part!
160:
Th-thank you! To tell the truth, I've
been practicing a bit lately.
163:
Though when I had to actually fight,
I was a bit startledit was so
different from how I imagined it!
167:
It's only natural. But you did more
than enoughit's clear you have the
makings of a fine mage!
177: They're... similar, in a way, yeah.
182:
Wow! The way they move is so
incredible! Where's the person
controlling them?
186:
I wonder what kind of magic they
employ... Where can I go to inspect
some of those golems for myself?
190:
Good question... You could maybe
ask a security company?
195:
All right, I see it now. The girl's got
some serious potential.
207:
Hello there. I wanted to train today
as well. I hope you don't mind.
211:
Nonsense. Your presence is most
welcome. You seem especially
eager to train lately.
216:
That's right. I felt really bad about
freezing up the other day in Qualia
City. I was... inadequate.
221:
What? No way, you were a huge
help to us!
225:
I'm afraid I still have far, far more to
learn. I need to be able to fight with
composure, no matter what
dangers I face.
228:
To do that, I need to study and
practice my magic even more!
233:
Yes, but make sure not to overexert
yourself. We'll lend you our aid
wherever possible as well.
237:
You will? In that case, could I ask you
to take me to even more different
worlds?
246:
How about we get going, then? We
were just about to head off to
Yamato.
257:
We'll be doing some shopping for
tonight's dinner. You can join us for
that too, if you'd like.
264:
Oh, if you don't mind me asking,
what's on the menu for tonight?
268:
Well, I haven't decided yet, but we've
got a load of bell peppers, so I'm
thinking of using them!
272:
O-oh... I guess I'll have to think extra
hard and work out a spell to change
the taste of peppers.
277:
Well, it seems that you haven't
outgrown all of your childish
tendencies quite yet.
285:
Don't treat me like a child! I thought I
made myself clear!
